00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:10.220
A wing coaster is a type of steel roller coaster
where pairs of riders sit on either side of

00:03:10.220 --> 00:03:13.270
the track and there is nothing above or below
them.

00:03:13.270 --> 00:03:18.400
The Gatekeeper, the fifth wing coaster in
the world, is located in Sandusky, OH.

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:25.269
Opened in 2013 and has the highest inversion
in the world measuring 170 ft. and in the

00:03:25.269 --> 00:03:30.460
wing coaster category it holds the record
for the longest, fastest, longest drop, and

00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:31.900
